'''Beyond the Pale''' was a publication company based in [[Northern Ireland]] which operated from 1988 to 2009.<ref>{{cite book|editor=Patrick Walsh, Clare Hutton|title=The Oxford History of the Irish Book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uxo7KTBKkJQC&lpg=PA324&dq=%22Beyond%20the%20Pale%22%20Northern%20Ireland&pg=PA324#v=onepage&q=%22Beyond%20the%20Pale%22%20Northern%20Ireland&f=false|volume=V|year=2011|publisher=OUP|isbn=0199249113|pages=323–324}}</ref> Their publications usually focused on controversial issues such as [[the troubles]].

The name refers to the idiom "[[The Pale|beyond the pale]]".

